import React from 'react'
import { Container, Row, Col, Image } from 'react-bootstrap';
import img1 from '../assets/grid1.jpg'
import img2 from '../assets/grid2.jpg'
import img3 from '../assets/grid3.jpg'
import img4 from '../assets/grid4.jpg'
import './MainGrid.css'

const MainGrid = () => {
  return (
    <Container className="mt-4">
    <Row>
      <Col md={6}>
        <Image src={img1} alt="Steve Madden" fluid className="mb-3" />
      </Col>
      <Col md={6}>
        <Row>
          <Col md={6}>
            <Image src={img2} alt="Superdry" fluid className="mb-3" />
          </Col>
          <Col md={6}>
            <Image src={img3} alt="Guess" fluid className="mb-3" />
          </Col>
        </Row>
        <Row>
          {/* Second Row: Single Image */}
          <Col>
            <Image src={img4} alt="Tommy Hilfiger" fluid />
          </Col>
        </Row>
      </Col>
    </Row>
  </Container>
  )
}

export default MainGrid
